snippet.title: Q: Python read file in DOT format and return city name list
snippet.description: citylist creates a list of city names with trailing spaces removed (easy using Python's strip() method). Two test cases are shown below, for lines at index 3 and 347. citylist … ("DOT500.txt")[3] 'TUCSON' citylist("DOT500.txt")[347] 'NORTH VILLE' and below is the DOT file(part of it) 1 958164 TOYOTA MOTOR CORPORATION TOYOTA LAND CRUISER 1994 19941223 N …
